definitions.definition: Any freshwater fish of the order Anguilliformes , which are elongated and resemble snakes .
Various other animals that resemble true eels, chiefly in shape :

subdefinitions.definition: Other ray-finned fishes : An electric eel (any knifefish of genus Electrophorus ) In order Synbranchiformes : A swamp eel (any fish in family Synbranchidae ). An earthworm eel , also called the spineless eel (any fish in family Chaudhuriidae ). A spiny eel (any fish in family Mastacembelidae ). A deep-sea spiny eel (any fish in family Notacanthidae ).

Certain amphibians : A conger eel , also called the Congo eel , amphiuma , and Congo snake (any salamander of genus Amphiuma ). A two-legged eel , also called the mud eel and lesser siren , Siren intermedia . A leopard eel , also called the leopard siren and reticulated siren , Siren reticulata . A rubber eel , Typhlonectes natans .
A vinegar eel , a roundworm of species Turbatrix aceti .

definitions.definition: Someone or something that is sneaky and/or hard to catch.
examples: That Dennis is a right eel , he always seems to slip away from the scene at the right time.
